The paper focuses on improving the performance of deep convolutional neural networks in computer vision tasks, specifically addressing challenges related to robustness and limited field of view. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a new architecture (IMEXnet) that adapts semi-implicit methods for partial differential equations, which could also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the architecture in semantic segmentation, which falls under the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of computational methods and neural networks could also make it relevant to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
